beer.beer_name: Wit a little help from my friends
beer.beer_description:
Beerbliotek #363

Citrus, crisp and bright.

The beer pours a hazy straw colour with a fluffy white head that lingers. Aromas of orange peel, coriander, and freshly baked bread fill the nose. On the palate, the beer is crisp and refreshing with a lively carbonation that enhances the citrus notes. Flavours of lemon, grapefruit, and spice lead to a dry, slightly bitter finish that leaves a pleasant tingle on the tongue. Overall, this is a bright and lively beer that is perfect for quenching your thirst on a hot summer day.
